  "intro_paragraph": "Burekas derive from the Turkish borek meaning filled pastry. These Sephardic treats traveled across the Ottoman Empire to become an Israeli staple. This plant-based version recreates the flaky texture and savory fillings without animal products. It captures the essence of traditional bakery culture in every golden bite.",
