    "generation_prompt": "A rustic, weathered wooden table set inside an authentic early 1900s stone kitchen in Safed displays a generous ceramic platter of golden-brown vegan burekas prepared in three distinct styles. In the center sits a substantial, flaky pastry roll filled with savory plant-based minced meat and rich tomato sauce, sliced to reveal the dark, textured filling. Arranged neatly around the roll are classic rectangular pockets filled with bright yellow turmeric-spiced mashed potatoes, their tops generously studded with white sesame seeds. Interspersed are intricate pinwheel-shaped pizza flower pastries, showcasing swirls of red tomato paste, chopped green olives, and melted dairy-free cheese. The puff pastry appears incredibly airy, flaky, and crisp, having been brushed with plant milk for a deep, appetizing golden sheen. Soft, warm natural light streams through a small arched window, casting gentle shadows and illuminating the texture of the ancient stone walls in the background. Fresh parsley sprigs and a small bowl of crushed tomatoes accompany the pastries on the table.",
